[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":973},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F20\u002Fjsweirdworld-37-iife-safe-code\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F20\u002Fjsweirdworld-37-iife-safe-code\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F20\u002Fjsweirdworld-37-iife-safe-code\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F20\u002Fjsweirdworld-37-iife-safe-code\u002F":948,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F20\u002Fjsweirdworld-37-iife-safe-code\u002F":957},"\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F20190520\u002F2719347754\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":931,"date":932,"description":933,"extension":934,"lang":935,"meta":936,"navigation":356,"path":937,"readingMinutes":938,"seo":939,"standalone":940,"stem":941,"tags":942,"tldr":945,"updated":932,"url":946,"__hash__":947},"content\u002Fen\u002FJsWeirdWorld\u002Fjsweirdworld-37-iife-safe-code.md","[JS Weird World] No.37 A Framework Tip: IIFEs and Safe Code","1000237573",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":926},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,122,125,128,135,138,141,203,210,269,274,283,367,372,375,378,461,467,470,564,570,583,684,689,692,775,781,784,901,906,909,913,922],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"We've already covered IIFEs earlier in this series, and a lot of well-known frameworks lean on this technique. So in this post I want to dig into IIFEs, safe code, and why this pattern is actually so useful.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"iife","IIFE",[17,25,26],{},"Here's an example from the course.",[28,29,34],"pre",{"className":30,"code":31,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\u002F\u002F IIFE\n(function(name) {\n  var greeting = 'Hello';\n  console.log(greeting + ' ' + name);\n})('Joun');\n","js","",[35,36,37,46,66,85,110],"code",{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,39,42],"span",{"class":40,"line":41},"line",1,[38,43,45],{"class":44},"sQrFR","\u002F\u002F IIFE\n",[38,47,49,53,57,59,63],{"class":40,"line":48},2,[38,50,52],{"class":51},"sMAXC","(",[38,54,56],{"class":55},"sWyjQ","function",[38,58,52],{"class":51},[38,60,62],{"class":61},"s_sBn","name",[38,64,65],{"class":51},") {\n",[38,67,69,72,75,78,82],{"class":40,"line":68},3,[38,70,71],{"class":55},"  var",[38,73,74],{"class":51}," greeting ",[38,76,77],{"class":55},"=",[38,79,81],{"class":80},"sTRMh"," 'Hello'",[38,83,84],{"class":51},";\n",[38,86,88,91,95,98,101,104,107],{"class":40,"line":87},4,[38,89,90],{"class":51},"  console.",[38,92,94],{"class":93},"sj_SG","log",[38,96,97],{"class":51},"(greeting ",[38,99,100],{"class":55},"+",[38,102,103],{"class":80}," ' '",[38,105,106],{"class":55}," +",[38,108,109],{"class":51}," name);\n",[38,111,113,116,119],{"class":40,"line":112},5,[38,114,115],{"class":51},"})(",[38,117,118],{"class":80},"'Joun'",[38,120,121],{"class":51},");\n",[17,123,124],{},"Let's start by looking at the execution stack to understand what's going on here.",[17,126,127],{},"Up top we've got our IIFE running, and because we wrapped it in parentheses and immediately invoked it, it created its own execution context.",[17,129,130],{},[131,132],"img",{"alt":133,"src":134},"Execution context","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FUBH8hBn.png",[17,136,137],{},"What this does is keep all the variables inside that function — they live inside the function, not in the global scope. So we can play around with that a bit.",[17,139,140],{},"Normally to output 1 through 10 you'd write something like this:",[28,142,144],{"className":30,"code":143,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"for(var i = 0 ; i \u003C 10; i++) {\n  console.log(i + 1);\n}\n",[35,145,146,182,198],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,147,148,151,153,156,159,161,165,168,171,174,177,180],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,149,150],{"class":55},"for",[38,152,52],{"class":51},[38,154,155],{"class":55},"var",[38,157,158],{"class":51}," i ",[38,160,77],{"class":55},[38,162,164],{"class":163},"sCcAr"," 0",[38,166,167],{"class":51}," ; i ",[38,169,170],{"class":55},"\u003C",[38,172,173],{"class":163}," 10",[38,175,176],{"class":51},"; i",[38,178,179],{"class":55},"++",[38,181,65],{"class":51},[38,183,184,186,188,191,193,196],{"class":40,"line":48},[38,185,90],{"class":51},[38,187,94],{"class":93},[38,189,190],{"class":51},"(i ",[38,192,100],{"class":55},[38,194,195],{"class":163}," 1",[38,197,121],{"class":51},[38,199,200],{"class":40,"line":68},[38,201,202],{"class":51},"}\n",[17,204,205,206,209],{},"After it finishes, let's check what ",[35,207,208],{},"i"," looks like now:",[28,211,213],{"className":30,"code":212,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"for(var i = 0 ; i \u003C 10; i++) {\n  console.log(i + 1);\n}\nconsole.log(i);\n",[35,214,215,241,255,259],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,216,217,219,221,223,225,227,229,231,233,235,237,239],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,218,150],{"class":55},[38,220,52],{"class":51},[38,222,155],{"class":55},[38,224,158],{"class":51},[38,226,77],{"class":55},[38,228,164],{"class":163},[38,230,167],{"class":51},[38,232,170],{"class":55},[38,234,173],{"class":163},[38,236,176],{"class":51},[38,238,179],{"class":55},[38,240,65],{"class":51},[38,242,243,245,247,249,251,253],{"class":40,"line":48},[38,244,90],{"class":51},[38,246,94],{"class":93},[38,248,190],{"class":51},[38,250,100],{"class":55},[38,252,195],{"class":163},[38,254,121],{"class":51},[38,256,257],{"class":40,"line":68},[38,258,202],{"class":51},[38,260,261,264,266],{"class":40,"line":87},[38,262,263],{"class":51},"console.",[38,265,94],{"class":93},[38,267,268],{"class":51},"(i);\n",[17,270,271],{},[131,272],{"alt":208,"src":273},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FOTnbOUb.png",[17,275,276,277,279,280,282],{},"You can see ",[35,278,208],{}," has become 10. If that's what you expected, fine, no problem. But what if it isn't? Say I only want ",[35,281,208],{}," to exist inside that loop — now we've got a problem. This is where an IIFE comes to the rescue:",[28,